==English==
===Etymology===
[[lunar]] + [[month]]

===Noun phrase===
'''lunar month'''
# a period from one [[new moon]] until the next.
# a [[synodic month]] of approximately 29.53 [[day]]s, measured from a [[lunar phase]] until the return of that same phase.
# a [[sidereal month]] of approximately 27.32 days, the length of the [[moon]]'s [[orbit]] about the [[Earth]].

